		<div id="comment_body_64702396">It's a PC with onboard hardware to do things like speech recognition and generation without going to the cloud.  Which creates an interesting tension between PC makers, who want to sell the capabilities to end-users, vs. service providers, who want everything to be cloud-based.
<p>
I don't rate the PC makers odds very highly, outside perhaps gaming which has been resistant to moving to the cloud due to latency.  Generative capabilities are sure to become integral to gaming.  Being limited to canned content is<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
