		<div id="comment_body_64702536">You can consider it pioneering or AI or not.  Did GPUs expand what a computer could do?  Computationally, no.  But eventually a GPU became a requirement to run games and certain other applications.  'AI' functionality is largely the same as the GPU, but some added functions like multiplying higher-dimensional tensors efficiently will eventually be required to run some applications.</div>
